{{page-title "Documentation — Overview"}}
<div class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl py-6 px-4 space-y-6">

  <Panel::Card>
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">Welcome to Career Caddy</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
      Job hunting is fragmented. Listings are spread across dozens of sites,
      applications live in browser tabs and mental notes, and by the time an
      interviewer asks "which role was this again?" you've forgotten the
      details. Career Caddy is a single place to track everything — and an AI
      partner that writes for you, in your voice.
    </p>
    {{! <img src="" alt="screenshot of Career Caddy dashboard" /> }}
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">The AI-First Philosophy</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
      Every AI feature in Career Caddy — scoring, cover letters, executive
      summaries, application answers — is powered by a single resource called
      <LinkTo @route="docs.career-data" class="text-accent-600 underline">Career
        Data</LinkTo>. Career Data is a markdown document you write once and
      refine over time. It describes your professional background, skills,
      writing style, and goals.
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
      Think of it as your permanent context window for the AI. The better your
      Career Data, the better every AI output.
      <strong>Start there before doing anything else.</strong>
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-600">
      Over time, answers and cover letters you mark as "favorites" are woven
      back into Career Data — the AI learns your voice from your own best work.
    </p>
    {{! <img src="" alt="diagram showing Career Data at center connecting to Scores, Cover Letters, Summaries, Answers" /> }}
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">Recommended Workflow</h2>
    <ol class="space-y-3 text-gray-600 list-decimal list-inside">
      <li>
        <strong>Build your Career Data</strong>
        — write your background, skills, and voice in markdown. This is your AI
        foundation. Spend real time here.
        <LinkTo @route="docs.career-data" class="text-accent-600 text-sm ml-1">→
          learn more</LinkTo>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Add a Job Post</strong>
        — paste in a listing manually or scrape it from a URL.
        <LinkTo @route="docs.job-posts" class="text-accent-600 text-sm ml-1">→
          learn more</LinkTo>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Generate a Score</strong>
        — the AI reads the job description and your Career Data and tells you
        how strong a fit you are (0–100) with a gap analysis.
        <LinkTo @route="docs.scores" class="text-accent-600 text-sm ml-1">→
          learn more</LinkTo>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Generate a Cover Letter</strong>
        — written in your voice, tailored to the role.
        <LinkTo
          @route="docs.cover-letters"
          class="text-accent-600 text-sm ml-1"
        >→ learn more</LinkTo>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Create a Job Application</strong>
        — link the job post to your resume and start tracking status as it
        progresses.
        <LinkTo
          @route="docs.job-applications"
          class="text-accent-600 text-sm ml-1"
        >→ learn more</LinkTo>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Capture and answer application questions</strong>
        — log questions you're asked. The AI drafts answers using your Career
        Data and the job context.
        <LinkTo @route="docs.questions" class="text-accent-600 text-sm ml-1">→
          learn more</LinkTo>
      </li>
    </ol>
    {{! <img src="" alt="screenshot showing the workflow steps in action" /> }}
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">Resources at a Glance</h2>
    <table class="w-full text-sm text-left text-gray-600">
      <thead>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
          <th class="pb-2 font-semibold text-gray-700 w-36">Resource</th>
          <th class="pb-2 font-semibold text-gray-700">What it does</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100">
        <tr class="py-2">
          <td class="py-2 font-medium">
            <LinkTo @route="docs.career-data" class="text-accent-600">Career
              Data</LinkTo>
          </td>
          <td class="py-2">Your professional background in markdown — the AI
            reads this for everything</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="py-2 font-medium">
            <LinkTo @route="docs.job-posts" class="text-accent-600">Job Posts</LinkTo>
          </td>
          <td class="py-2">Stored job listings — the root resource everything
            else attaches to</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="py-2 font-medium">
            <LinkTo
              @route="docs.job-applications"
              class="text-accent-600"
            >Applications</LinkTo>
          </td>
          <td class="py-2">Your record of applying — tracks status, dates,
            notes, and linked Q&A</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="py-2 font-medium">
            <LinkTo
              @route="docs.resumes"
              class="text-accent-600"
            >Resumes</LinkTo>
          </td>
          <td class="py-2">Structured resume data — importable, editable, used
            to supplement AI context</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="py-2 font-medium">
            <LinkTo @route="docs.cover-letters" class="text-accent-600">Cover
              Letters</LinkTo>
          </td>
          <td class="py-2">AI-generated letters in your voice, tied to a
            specific job post</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="py-2 font-medium">
            <LinkTo
              @route="docs.companies"
              class="text-accent-600"
            >Companies</LinkTo>
          </td>
          <td class="py-2">Employer profiles that group related posts,
            applications, and Q&A</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="py-2 font-medium">
            <LinkTo
              @route="docs.questions"
              class="text-accent-600"
            >Questions</LinkTo>
          </td>
          <td class="py-2">Application questions captured from postings — AI can
            draft answers</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="py-2 font-medium">
            <LinkTo
              @route="docs.answers"
              class="text-accent-600"
            >Answers</LinkTo>
          </td>
          <td class="py-2">Your responses — multiple drafts per question,
            favorites feed back to AI</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="py-2 font-medium">
            <LinkTo @route="docs.scores" class="text-accent-600">Scores</LinkTo>
          </td>
          <td class="py-2">AI fit score (0–100) of your profile vs. a job
            description with gap analysis</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="py-2 font-medium">
            <LinkTo
              @route="docs.summaries"
              class="text-accent-600"
            >Summaries</LinkTo>
          </td>
          <td class="py-2">AI-generated executive summaries tailored to a
            specific role</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="py-2 font-medium">
            <LinkTo
              @route="docs.scrapes"
              class="text-accent-600"
            >Scrapes</LinkTo>
          </td>
          <td class="py-2">Raw webpage captures of job listings — the input that
            becomes a Job Post</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="py-2 font-medium">
            <LinkTo
              @route="docs.extension-privacy"
              class="text-accent-600"
            >Extension Privacy</LinkTo>
          </td>
          <td class="py-2">Privacy policy for the Career Caddy Sender browser
            extension — what's read, when, and where it goes</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </Panel::Card>

</div>